[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  **What was built — `bst.zig`**\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  \u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | Concern | Decision |\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[38;5;238m  |---|---|\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Generic** | `BST(comptime T, comptime compareFn)` — works for any ordered type |\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Memory** | `GeneralPurposeAllocator` in `main`; `std.testing.allocator` in tests — both detect leaks |\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Insert** | Recursive; duplicates silently ignored; `len` incremented only on new node |\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Search** | Iterative (no stack growth); returns `?*T` so caller can mutate in place |\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Delete** | All three cases: leaf, one child, two children (in-order successor swap); absent value is no-op |\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Traversals** | In-order, pre-order, post-order — comptime `visitFn` callback, zero allocation |\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Height** | Recursive utility; empty tree returns 0 |\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  | **Comparators** | `compareI32` and `compareU32` provided; plug in any `fn(T,T) Order` |\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  **Run it:**\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  ```sh\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  zig run bst.zig        # example output\u001b[0m\r\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[38;5;238m  zig test bst.zig       # 10 tests\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;5;238m  ```\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b8"]
